docs.lead_paragraph: RED BANK, N.J., Dec. 31. -- An exciting race marked by a close finish occurred to-day under the direction of the North Shrewsbury River Yacht Club. A fine breeze blew from the west, causing the yachts to lift at frequent intervals. The warm wind softened the surface of the ice, and the sharp runners of the boats sank deeply in the slush, which materially retarded their speed.

docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Jan. 1. -- Hurricanelike storms have been prevailing in the greater part of Germany during the last twenty-four hours, accompanied by rain and snow. The storm was worst on the Baltic coast, where northwest and northeast winds drove the water into all the harbors. Kiel, Eckernforde, Flensburg, Lubeck, Hadersleben, Stralsund, Greifswald, and other towns are partly flooded, and considerable damage has been done to sea-bathing establishments.

docs.lead_paragraph: Directed by Police Captain Linderman of the Sheeepshead Bay Precinct, a search was made there yesterday for Catharine Bierman, the young German girl who disappeared from the St. Clair Hotel, Sheepshead Bay, eleven days ago. The Captain had a sand pit near the hotel dragged for the girl's body, but without success. Late yesterday afternoon he declared it to be his belief that she had been kidnapped by some unknown person in Manhattan.

Harris, aged forty-five years, of Beverly, Mass., for several years a specialist in the Bureau of Entomology of the Agricultural Department, was found dead in his room in a hotel here to-day. docs.lead_paragraph: To prevent appendicitis: (1) Do not neglect chills when heated by exercise, especially after games on grass, or when much fatigued in mind or body. docs.lead_paragraph: CAMBRIDGE, Mass., Jan. 24. -- Charles L. Tucker of Auburndale at 10:10 o'clock to-night was found guilty of the murder, in the first degree, of Miss Mabel Page in her father's home, in Weston, on March 31 last. A more disastrous conflagration was only prevented by the heroic efforts of the entire Fire Department of Omaha, which was reinforced by aid from South Omaha and Council Bluffs.
